# Keep the build context lean: skip everything we don't need to copy into the image.

# Git
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# IDE / editor
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache

# Docker itself
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml

# Docs / misc
README.md
LICENSE
*.md

# Build output
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/out/
**/publish/
**/[Dd]ebug/
**/[Rr]elease/
# `mise run publish` output — the build stage regenerates this itself
artifacts/

# Node (front-end tooling via Vite + Tailwind)
**/node_modules/
**/npm-debug.log
**/yarn-error.log
# Vite output is rebuilt inside the image by the `client` stage — never bake host artifacts in
**/dist/
**/.vite/

# Code-first uSync bundle output — regenerated inside the image by the `usync-bundle`
# stage from Aesys.Core/, never copied from the (possibly stale) host working tree.
Aesys.Web/uSync/v17/ContentTypes/
Aesys.Web/uSync/v17/Dictionary/

# Umbraco runtime artefacts that must never be baked into the image
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Data/TEMP/
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Data/CreatedPackages/
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Data/*.sqlite.db
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Data/*.sqlite.db-shm
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Data/*.sqlite.db-wal
Aesys.Web/umbraco/Logs/
Aesys.Web/wwwroot/media/

# JSON schemas regenerated on each build
Aesys.Web/appsettings-schema.json
Aesys.Web/appsettings-schema.*.json
Aesys.Web/umbraco-package-schema.json

# Tooling (host-only, never needed inside the image)
# .mise.toml is NOT excluded — the build stage installs mise and runs `mise run`
# tasks, so it needs the task definitions. .mise.local.toml stays excluded: it's a
# gitignored per-developer override file and must never be baked into a shared image.
.mise.local.toml
.config/
docker-compose*.yml
